Merged in comms_deadlock (pull request #273)

Fix deadlock between Transport thread and ROS service callbacks

Approved-by: Nate Koenig <natekoenig@gmail.com>

message.raw:
Fix deadlock between Transport thread and ROS service callbacks

This fixes a deadlock that occurs when `SubtRosRelay::OnPoseFromArtifact` is called concurrently with `SubtRosRelay::OnMessage`. Consider two `subt_seed_node`s with robot names X1 and X2. Let's say X2 sends a message to X1. This is a call to `SubtRosRelay::OnSendTo` which sends the request to Transport and returns immediately. In the mean time, let's say X1 calls `SubtRosRelay::OnPoseFromArtifact`. Since X1 is single threaded node, this call is blocking. Now, if it happens that Tranport is ready to send the message from X2 to X1, it will invoke `SubtRosRelay::OnMessage` from a separate thread. This will in turn make a service call to X1 which happens to be blocking on its service call to `SubtRosRelay::OnPoseFromArtifact`.

The solution I found is to use a lock free data structure to queue up messages when they arrive at `SubtRosRelay::OnMessage` and process them in a separate thread.
